cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with image generation, specifically generating complex scenes with multiple objects. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel Scene-Graph Similarity Module (SGSM) and changes to the conditioning mechanism of the generator, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper introduces a new evaluation metric, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves understanding the relationships between objects in a scene.
